  "texts": [
    "Whereas that format was easy to process using popular Python libraries, on the other hand, its maintenance was extremely tedious and prone to introducing issues.",
    "Since each row contained repeated snippets from other prompts, any refinement in a snippet implied that it was necessary to (1) locate all the prompts that were affected (i.e., contained that snippet) and ( 2) apply that change manually (which, obviously, could lead to inconsistencies, out-of-date prompts, or errors).",
    "To improve the maintainability of LangBiTe's library, we have established a strategy to translate the different columns that compose a prompt into elements of the Impromptu language.To begin with, a prefix is directly defined as a text literal snippet, which could then be referenced by multiple prompts.",
    "Similarly, all core texts are text literals, but since they are unique, they are referenced only by a single prompt.",
    "We have decided to split the output formatting instructions into more atomic snippets and then include them within a composer referenced by the original prompts."
  ],
